Sherman Millions Inc., a home decorating retailer, has contracted you to develop an interactive calculator widget for their website that will help a shopper determine the cost of painting a room. When the user enters # of square feet needing paint, # of square feet a can will cover, the cost of a can, and the desired color, the widget will calculate how many cans are needed (rounding up) and the total cost of the paint job. The results of these two calculations are displayed within the widget. (Note: none of these values are currently provided on the website, except for the 5 available paint colors.)

You will submit your work on this project by editing the provided HTML document, writing the necessary JavaScript within the <script> tag, and editing any other element(s) in the document necessary for completion of your task.

Your project performance will be evaluated via the scale below:

Level 0 (35 points) - near-functional, concept-mapped:
All the necessary script steps are mapped in pseudocode, ready for line-by-line translation into JavaScript. Any necessary edits to the HTML are completed. Some JavaScript is written.

Level 1 (40 points) - functional, proof-of-concept:
All of the above, plus:
The widget executes successfully when the user enters appropriate information as described above.

Level 2 (45 points) - functional, production-ready:
All of the above, plus:
The widget validates the userâ€™s input to ensure that valid inputs are entered, returning an alert message whenever an invalid input is entered.

Level 3 (50 points) - functional, elegant:
All of the above, plus:
The widget displays the user-selected paint color in a small square in the widget, near the output fields.
-->
